The textbook is Rivstart B1 (by Paula Levy Scherrer and Karl Lindemalm). Extra materials will be delivered during the classes. Active participation is expected. There will be a lot of group work and many independent tasks.
Every two weeks an extract from Swedish modern fiction is read and translated. We watch TV broadcasts and listen to the news broadcast on the radio. We will read newspaper articles and discuss current topics. 
In grammar the focus will be on verb and adverb.
A film night will be organised.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to learn Swedish with the stress on the general vocabulary and grammar to be used in conversations and presentations.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  A student who has passed the course is able to 1. follow both written and oral texts on the relevant level, find out the essence of the text; 2. take notes and use them in the form of discussion and/or presentation; 3.deliver a presentation on a general topic; 4. understand the peers' presentations on the required level, discuss the topics and ask the questions
